  "text": "The work in [CITATION_1] proposes what the authors call a progressive deep CNN structure (Fig. 20 ) that develop HR depth images by a gradual learning of the higher frequencies. Supplementary information in the form of depth field statistics and color-depth correlation serves as two priors provide complement to the CNN for further refinement of depth maps.The authors argue that the method is equally good in the absence of HR color images whereby the depth images by themselves are enough to refine the depth images. The reported results compare the method with more than a dozen state of the art methods applied to standard datasets and the results establish the superiority of the method.",
